headline: AutoZone Stock Falls After 5th Straight Earnings Miss. Why It’s Still Up 29% This Year.
summary: Shares of  AutoZone  were falling Tuesday after the company missed earnings expectations for the fifth consecutive quarter.  The automotive parts retailer posted adjusted earnings of $48.71 a share for its fiscal fourth quarter, short of Wall Street’s consensus call for $50.57.  “We expect to aggressively open stores in the new year as we continue to focus on growing our market share over time,” said CEO Phil Daniele.
